value.title: Biden dismisses record economic growth as not 'nearly enough' to dig out of 'deep' recession
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden dismissed the U.S. economy's record-shattering growth as not "nearly enough" to get the country out of a "deep hole" on Thursday.

value.title: Former Democrat Rubin on why he is voting for Trump: 'No feeling of patriotism' on the left anymore
value.excerpt: President Trump is the last bastion to stopping the radical left, talk show host Dave Rubin said Thursday.

value.title: Joe Biden is a 'Trojan Horse' for socialism, says Tammy Bruce
value.excerpt: 2020 Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden is being used as a "trojan horse," Fox News contributor Tammy Bruce said on Thursday.

value.title: Watch: Barack Obama Campaigns For Joe Biden At Orlando, Florida Event
value.excerpt: Former President Barack Obama will campaign for Joe Biden at an Orlando, Florida event on Tuesday afternoon, one week ahead of the 2020 election.

value.title: Trump Jr. warns election is 'about freedom versus tyranny, capitalism versus socialism and Communism'
value.excerpt: The Democrats' "endgame" is to transform America into a far-left, Marxist state where dissent is not permitted, Donald Trump Jr. told "Hannity" Wednesday night.

value.title: Rick Scott makes 'six-figure' ad buy for Trump in Florida: Report
value.excerpt: The pro-Trump ads will run in six to eight Florida media markets

value.title: Buttigieg defends Biden, claims Dems 'would have chosen somebody else' if they wanted fracking ban
value.excerpt: "The Story" host Martha MacCallum pressed Joe Biden campaign surrogate Pete Buttigieg Wednesday over the 2020 Democratic nominee's position on fracking and the oil industry following repeated attempts to clarify earlier comments on the issue.

value.title: WSJ Opinion: Vote for Joe Biden? Seriously?
value.excerpt: Joe Biden is Bernie Sanders in sheep’s clothing. Compared to the Democrats’ grim vision of America, President Trump is the optimist. Images: AFP/Ge

value.title: Trump says Miles Taylor 'should be prosecuted' after reveal as 'Anonymous' administration critic
value.excerpt: President Trump called Wednesday night for former Department of Homeland Security chief of staff Miles Taylor to face prosecution after he revealed himself as “Anonymous,” the former senior administration official who authored a New York Times op-ed criticizing the presidency in 2018.

value.title: White House’s Stephen Miller warns of ‘nationwide catch and release’ if Biden is elected
value.excerpt: White House adviser Stephen Miller on Wednesday warned of a policy of “nationwide catch and release” if Democratic nominee Joe Biden is elected to the White House -- painting a stark contrast with the Trump administration’s stance on immigration.

value.title: Ben Shapiro calls Biden a 'gateway drug to radicalism', not a return to normalcy
value.excerpt: Joe Biden has based his presidential campaign on a promise to restore "normalcy" if he unseats President Trump, but the former vice president will act as nothing more than "a gateway drug to radicalism,

value.title: Ari Fleischer: Biden is 'taking advantage of' a 'broken-down media' that is 'biased against Trump'
value.excerpt: The Biden campaign is "taking advantage" of the media bias against President Trump to keep the controversy surrounding former Vice President Joe Biden's son Hunter out of the spotlight, former White House Press Secretary Ari Fleischer claimed Wednesday.

value.title: Trump: Philadelphia police shooting a 'terrible event,' but rioting comes from group Joe Biden 'supports'
value.excerpt: President Trump called on Democrats in Philadelphia to crack down on recent rioting, and blamed Joe Biden for not condemning the unrest strongly enough.

value.title: Joe Biden could be compromised by Chinese Communist Party: Rep. Crenshaw
value.excerpt: Joe Biden needs to answer whether or not he's compromised by China before the Nov. 3 election, Rep. Dan Crenshaw, R-Texas, said Wednesday.

value.title: Hunter Biden engaged in ‘raw influence-peddling’ on grand, global scale: Turley
value.excerpt: Joe Biden and his family engaged in "legal corruption" despite claims of no wrongdoing, Fox News contributor Jonathan Turley argued Wednesday.

value.title: Ricky Martin says it's 'super sad' to see fellow Latinos back Donald Trump
value.excerpt: Ricky Martin discussed his support for Joe Biden and the “super sad” prospect of seeing fellow Latinos vote for Donald Trump.

value.title: Rehire Trump as national CEO to continue US economic renaissance: Steve Cortes
value.excerpt: President Trump will continue the thriving economy if re-elected, but Joe Biden threatens a reversal, Trump 2020 campaign senior adviser Steve Cortes told "Fox & Friends."

value.title: Election 6 days away: Biden back in Delaware as Trump heads to Arizona
value.excerpt: President Trump will hold two campaign rallies in the battleground state of Arizona on Wednesday as his Democratic rival Joe Biden, back in his home state of Delaware, hears a briefing from public health officials on the coronavirus pandemic with just six days left until the election.

value.title: 'Squad' member Ayanna Pressley to stump for Biden in New Hampshire
value.excerpt: Rep. Ayanna Pressley, D-Mass., will stump in New Hampshire Thursday for Joe Biden, making her the first “Squad” member to officially campaign for the Democratic nominee.

value.title: Tony Bobulinski tells Tucker: Joe Biden denials of involvement in son's business 'a blatant lie'
value.excerpt: Tony Bobulinski, a former business associate of Hunter Biden, will tell "Tucker Carlson Tonight" in an exclusive interview Tuesday evening that Joe Biden's denials of knowledge or involvement in his son's foreign dealings are "a blatant lie."

value.title: CBP chief warns of border 'invasion' with liberal policies, reversal of Trump-era efforts
value.excerpt: The United States could face an "invasion" that would make the recent migrant crisis seem relatively tame if President Trump's efforts are reversed, and Democratic policies incentivize illegal border crossings, Acting Customs and Border Protection Commissioner Mark Morgan told reporters on Tuesday.

value.title: Biden makes plea to ‘unite and heal’ the country during stop in Georgia
value.excerpt: Joe Biden, playing offense in a long time red state turned crucial battleground this year, made a closing campaign pitch on Tuesday for national unity to rise above what he called the division President Trump’s sown during his four years in the White House.

value.title: McEnany: Joe Biden’s comments on oil, fracking will be ‘death knell’ of his campaign
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential hopeful Joe Biden "lost" Pennsylvania in the election after his comments on banning the oil and fracking industry, White House press secretary Kayleigh McEnany said on Tuesday.

value.title: Trump already chose Barrett successor on appeals court, confirmation possible regardless of election outcome
value.excerpt: With Justice Amy Coney Barrett now on the Supreme Court, a new vacancy has opened on the 7th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals where she previously sat, and President Trump has already named the person he plans to have replace her on that bench.

value.title: Ilhan Omar mobilizing progressives to push Biden further left
value.excerpt: Rep. Ilhan Omar, D-Minn., said in an interview that Democrats will have "a cohort of progressives" who will try to influence 2020 presidential nominee Joe Biden should he be elected.

value.title: Biden again clarifies oil 'transition' comment, says industry 'not going to go away'
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden on Monday clarified his oil industry "transition" comment in two separate interviews with TV stations in Pittsburgh and Dallas.

value.title: Biden raises idea of rotating Supreme Court justices: 'There is some literature among constitutional scholars'
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Joe Biden indicated on Monday that he might be open to shifting Supreme Court justices to lower courts if elected president, noting that he hadn't made any "judgement" yet on the issue.

value.title: Civil rights attorney Leo Terrell: Biden has done nothing for Black community 'other than insulting' them
value.excerpt: Civil rights attorney Leo Terrell rips 2020 Democratic nominee Joe Biden for his failure to address issues impacting the Black community during his 36-year career in the United States Senate on his new Fox Nation show "Larry & Leo 2.

value.title: Pence campaigns with 'medically informed' approach to events after staffers test positive for COVID-19
value.excerpt: Vice President Pence has returned to the campaign trail after key staffers tested positive for the novel coronavirus, however his team is taking a “thoughtful” and “medically-informed” approach to his travel this week in the final stretch until Election Day.

value.title: Kamala Harris thinks she can laugh her way through serious questions: Pavlich
value.excerpt: Editor Katie Pavlich called Democratic vice-presidential nominee Sen. Kamala Harris “the most far-left Democrat in Washington, D.C.," and said Joe Biden picked her to "make sure that the left wing of the party felt comfortable" that they would have a voice in his administration.
